    <h1>üç± <i>Japanese Cuisine</i> üç£</h1>

    <p><b>Japanese cuisine</b> emphasizes seasonal ingredients, visual presentation, and harmony of flavor.</p>

    <h2>Popular Japanese Dishes</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Sushi</b> - Rice with raw fish or vegetables</li>
        <li><i>Ramen</i> - Noodle soup with various toppings</li>
        <li>Tempura - Lightly battered and fried seafood or vegetables</li>
        <li>Okonomiyaki - Japanese savory pancake</li>
        <li>Mochi - Sweet rice cake</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Essential Ingredients</h2>
    <ol>
        <li>Soy sauce</li>
        <li>Mirin (sweet rice wine)</li>
        <li>Miso paste</li>
        <li>Seaweed (Nori)</li>
        <li>Wasabi</li>
    </ol>

